Operatives of the Nigeria Police Force in the Federal Capital Territory Command have rescued two kids locked up in a toilet by their guardian, Mrs Loveth Ilobi, who has been arrested by the police. She would be prosecuted at the end of the investigation, the police said. FCT Police Command spokesperson, DSP Anjuguri Manzah, in a statement, said, acting on a tip-off on Friday, some operatives “rescued two children who were allegedly locked in a toilet and subjected to inhuman treatment by their guardian who lives on the second floor of a two-storey building in FCDA Quarters, Garki. “One of the children, Wisdom Christopher King Chidemi, male, 9, who miraculously escaped through the window of their guardian’s apartment located in the building, raised the alarm that led to the rescue of the second Angel Nwoga, female, also 9-years-old from the apartment.” “Mrs Ilobi, was reported to have been subjecting the children to undue hardship and inhuman treatment; information has it that she often starve the children of food and locked them up in the toilet till she returns from work late at night. “Police said investigation is ongoing.”